  "notes_normalized": "Cannabis is legal in Illinois under state law for recreational adult use. Medical cannabis is also legal under a regulated state program in Illinois. Cannabis remains federally illegal in United States. Possession is limited to Up to 30 g flower or 5 g concentrate (adult).",
  "notes_raw": "style=\"background:#196E92;\" | {{Hs|1}} A first in the nation, Illinois will also expunge an estimated 700,000 marijuana-related police records and court convictions in a phased approach forecast to be completed by 2025. On December 31, 2020, Governor JB Pritzker announced that his administration granted pardons for 9,210 low-level cannabis convictions and the wiping of 492,000 non-felony cannabis-related arrest records.",
